chunks.content: SS304 steel: Austenitic stainless steel with excellent corrosion resistance. Chemical composition: chromium: 18-20%, nickel: 8-10.5%, carbon: max 0.08%, manganese: max 2%, silicon: max 0.75%, phosphorus: max 0.045%, sulfur: max 0.03%, iron: balance. Mechanical properties: yieldStrength: 205 MPa minimum, tensileStrength: 515 MPa minimum, elongation: 40% minimum, hardness: HB 201 max. Physical properties: density: 8.0 g/cm³, meltingPoint: 1400-1450°C, thermalConductivity: 16.2 W/m·K, electricalResistivity: 0.72 μΩ·m. Applications: Food processing equipment, Kitchen appliances, Chemical containers, Architectural panels. Thickness range: 0.5-50mm. Width range: 1000-2000mm. Standard codes: ASTM A240, EN 10088-2, JIS G4304.

SS316 steel: Molybdenum-bearing austenitic stainless steel with superior corrosion resistance. Chemical composition: chromium: 16-18%, nickel: 10-14%, molybdenum: 2-3%, carbon: max 0.08%, manganese: max 2%, silicon: max 0.75%, phosphorus: max 0.045%, sulfur: max 0.03%, iron: balance. Mechanical properties: yieldStrength: 205 MPa minimum, tensileStrength: 515 MPa minimum, elongation: 40% minimum, hardness: HB 217 max. Physical properties: density: 8.0 g/cm³, meltingPoint: 1375-1400°C, thermalConductivity: 16.2 W/m·K, electricalResistivity: 0.74 μΩ·m. Applications: Marine environments, Pharmaceutical equipment, Food grade applications, Chemical processing. Thickness range: 0.5-50mm. Width range: 1000-2000mm. Standard codes: ASTM A240, EN 10088-2, JIS G4304.

SS410 steel: Martensitic stainless steel with good strength and moderate corrosion resistance. Chemical composition: chromium: 11.5-13.5%, carbon: 0.08-0.15%, manganese: max 1%, silicon: max 1%, phosphorus: max 0.04%, sulfur: max 0.03%, iron: balance. Mechanical properties: yieldStrength: 275 MPa minimum, tensileStrength: 450 MPa minimum, elongation: 20% minimum, hardness: HB 159-200. Physical properties: density: 7.7 g/cm³, meltingPoint: 1480-1530°C, thermalConductivity: 24.9 W/m·K, electricalResistivity: 0.57 μΩ·m. Applications: Valves and pumps, Shafts and spindles, Cutlery, Machine parts. Thickness range: 1-100mm. Width range: 1000-2500mm. Standard codes: ASTM A240, EN 10088-2.

SS430 steel: Ferritic stainless steel with good formability and moderate corrosion resistance. Chemical composition: chromium: 16-18%, carbon: max 0.12%, manganese: max 1%, silicon: max 0.75%, phosphorus: max 0.04%, sulfur: max 0.03%, iron: balance. Mechanical properties: yieldStrength: 205 MPa minimum, tensileStrength: 450 MPa minimum, elongation: 22% minimum, hardness: HB 183 max. Physical properties: density: 7.7 g/cm³, meltingPoint: 1425-1510°C, thermalConductivity: 26.0 W/m·K, electricalResistivity: 0.60 μΩ·m. Applications: Automotive trim, Kitchen equipment, Architectural applications, Washing machine drums. Thickness range: 0.5-6mm. Width range: 1000-1500mm. Standard codes: ASTM A240, EN 10088-2.

SS321 steel: Titanium-stabilized austenitic stainless steel with excellent high-temperature properties. Chemical composition: chromium: 17-19%, nickel: 9-12%, titanium: 5x carbon content minimum, carbon: max 0.08%, manganese: max 2%, silicon: max 0.75%, phosphorus: max 0.045%, sulfur: max 0.03%, iron: balance. Mechanical properties: yieldStrength: 205 MPa minimum, tensileStrength: 515 MPa minimum, elongation: 40% minimum, hardness: HB 201 max. Physical properties: density: 8.0 g/cm³, meltingPoint: 1400-1425°C, thermalConductivity: 16.2 W/m·K, electricalResistivity: 0.72 μΩ·m. Applications: High-temperature applications, Aircraft exhaust systems, Heat exchangers, Welding equipment. Thickness range: 0.5-50mm. Width range: 1000-2000mm. Standard codes: ASTM A240, EN 10088-2.

Procedure PROC-001: Quality Control Inspection for Thickness Variation
Steps: Measure thickness at minimum 5 points across the width using calibrated micrometer
Record measurements at center, quarter points, and edges
Calculate average thickness and compare to specification tolerance
If variation exceeds ±0
1mm, mark material for review
Document all measurements in quality log
Notify production supervisor if out of tolerance
Procedure PROC-002: Surface Finish Inspection
Steps: Clean surface with appropriate solvent
Use surface roughness tester at multiple locations
Measure Ra (arithmetic average roughness) value
Compare against specification (typically Ra ≤ 0
4μm for food grade)
Document measurements
Reject if surface finish does not meet requirements
Procedure PROC-003: Chemical Composition Verification
Steps: Obtain sample from production batch
Prepare sample for spectroscopy analysis
Perform XRF or OES analysis
Verify chromium, nickel, and other alloying elements
Compare results to grade specification
Document and archive test results
Procedure PROC-004: Handling Scrap Material
Steps: Separate scrap by steel grade to prevent contamination
Measure and record scrap quantity
Assess scrap quality and reusability
Store reusable scrap in designated area by grade
Dispose of non-reusable scrap according to environmental regulations
Update inventory system with scrap quantities
Procedure PROC-005: Safety Guidelines for Hot Rolling Operations
Steps: Ensure all personnel wear appropriate PPE (heat-resistant gloves, face shields)
Verify equipment safety interlocks are functional
Check material temperature before handling
Maintain safe distance from hot material (minimum 2 meters)
Use proper lifting equipment for hot material
Report any safety incidents immediately
